will not yet be publicly

00:04:30.906 --> 00:04:31.496 A:middle
accessible.

00:04:32.456 --> 00:04:34.116 A:middle
You will, however, be able to

00:04:34.116 --> 00:04:35.076 A:middle
white list some of your

00:04:35.076 --> 00:04:36.926 A:middle
employees who will be able to

00:04:37.086 --> 00:04:38.696 A:middle
test your end-to-end experience

00:04:39.006 --> 00:04:40.166 A:middle
to make sure that you're ready.

00:04:40.846 --> 00:04:45.056 A:middle
So let's talk about how we're

00:04:45.056 --> 00:04:46.446 A:middle
making it easy for your

00:04:46.446 --> 00:04:48.726 A:middle
customers to find you and to

00:04:48.726 --> 00:04:50.006 A:middle
start a conversation with your

00:04:50.006 --> 00:04:50.496 A:middle
business.

00:04:51.636 --> 00:04:53.106 A:middle
Once you have your Business Chat

00:04:53.106 --> 00:04:54.916 A:middle
account, message buttons will

00:04:54.916 --> 00:04:56.706 A:middle
start appearing throughout iOS.

00:04:58.706 --> 00:05:00.446 A:middle
For example, this is how it

00:05:00.446 --> 00:05:01.366 A:middle
would look in Safari.

00:05:02.216 --> 00:05:03.856 A:middle
Customer might type your website

00:05:04.766 --> 00:05:06.036 A:middle
and a search result would appear

00:05:06.036 --> 00:05:07.346 A:middle
that highlights your business.

00:05:08.336 --> 00:05:10.566 A:middle
In this example, the user typed

00:05:10.566 --> 00:05:12.786 A:middle
"apple" and the search result

00:05:12.786 --> 00:05:14.656 A:middle
shows the nearby Apple Union

00:05:14.656 --> 00:05:15.436 A:middle
Square location.

00:05:15.436 --> 00:05:17.566 A:middle
And you can see that the message

00:05:17.616 --> 00:05:18.926 A:middle
button is prominently featured.

00:05:20.456 --> 00:05:21.806 A:middle
Your user can start a

00:05:21.806 --> 00:05:24.076 A:middle
conversation right from here

00:05:24.076 --> 00:05:25.086 A:middle
instead of hunting on the

00:05:25.086 --> 00:05:25.976 A:middle
website for contact information.

00:05:26.776 --> 00:05:31.506 A:middle
Here is the Message button in

00:05:31.506 --> 00:05:36.096 A:middle
Search and in Siri and in Maps

00:05:37.556 --> 00:05:38.136 A:middle
too.

00:05:38.466 --> 00:05:40.926 A:middle
The Message button can appear

00:05:41.116 --> 00:05:42.116 A:middle
for each one of your store

00:05:42.116 --> 00:05:42.926 A:middle
locations.

00:05:43.476 --> 00:05:47.586 A:middle
We are also adding new support

00:05:47.636 --> 00:05:49.106 A:middle
for businesses that don't have

00:05:49.106 --> 00:05:50.896 A:middle
locations, including those that

00:05:50.896 --> 00:05:52.696 A:middle
might be online or app only.

00:05:53.966 --> 00:05:54.866 A:middle
Now if you're an online

00:05:54.866 --> 00:05:56.346 A:middle
business, or if there're no

00:05:56.346 --> 00:05:57.406 A:middle
nearby locations, there will

00:05:57.406 --> 00:05:58.806 A:middle
still be a search result

00:05:58.806 --> 00:05:59.766 A:middle
available for you.

00:06:00.596 --> 00:06:01.986 A:middle
This is how search results might

00:06:01.986 --> 00:06:04.116 A:middle
look in Safari if Apple had no

00:06:04.116 --> 00:06:05.476 A:middle
nearby store locations.

00:06:05.936 --> 00:06:10.406 A:middle
Links are another great entry

00:06:10.406 --> 00:06:12.316 A:middle
point that you can use to invite

00:06:12.416 --> 00:06:14.076 A:middle
your customers into your

00:06:14.076 --> 00:06:15.396 A:middle
Business Chat conversation.

00:06:17.116 --> 00:06:18.466 A:middle
You can put links on your

00:06:18.466 --> 00:06:21.516 A:middle
websites, in your app, and in

00:06:21.516 --> 00:06:22.256 A:middle
your emails.

00:06:23.326 --> 00:06:24.846 A:middle
When your customer taps your

00:06:24.846 --> 00:06:27.056 A:middle
link, it will open your Business

00:06:27.056 --> 00:06:29.416 A:middle
Chat conversation on supporting

00:06:29.416 --> 00:06:31.576 A:middle
devices within the Messages app.

00:06:32.866 --> 00:06:34.936 A:middle
To create your link, you'll need

00:06:34.936 --> 00:06:38.706 A:middle
your Business Chat ID, which you

00:06:38.706 --> 00:06:40.076 A:middle
will receive after you create

00:06:40.076 --> 00:06:41.366 A:middle
your account.

00:06:44.256 --> 00:06:45.586 A:middle
The next feature that I'd like

00:06:45.586 --> 00:06:47.146 A:middle
to review is something called

00:06:47.146 --> 00:06:47.836 A:middle
Chat Intent.

00:06:48.856 --> 00:06:51.296 A:middle
Chat Intent is a great way to

00:06:51.296 --> 00:06:52.746 A:middle
provide better support to your

00:06:52.746 --> 00:06:55.136 A:middle
customers by helping you

00:06:55.136 --> 00:06:57.116 A:middle
understand the context of their

00:06:57.116 --> 00:06:57.626 A:middle
question.

00:06:59.056 --> 00:07:01.096 A:middle
When you create links, you can

00:07:01.096 --> 00:07:02.996 A:middle
tag them to identify where your

00:07:02.996 --> 00:07:05.586 A:middle
customer tapped or clicked it.

00:07:06.636 --> 00:07:08.456 A:middle
There are two Chat Intent values

00:07:08.496 --> 00:07:09.316 A:middle
that you can use.

00:07:10.046 --> 00:07:11.796 A:middle
The first one is called intent

00:07:11.796 --> 00:07:14.796 A:middle
ID and the second one is group

00:07:14.796 --> 00:07:16.466 A:middle
ID, and they're completely

00:07:16.466 --> 00:07:16.936 A:middle
optional.

00:07:17.686 --> 00:07:18.876 A:middle
They could be whatever you need

00:07:18.876 --> 00:07:19.346 A:middle
them to be.

00:07:20.726 --> 00:07:22.146 A:middle
When your customer taps your

00:07:22.146 --> 00:07:24.426 A:middle
link and that link contains Chat

00:07:24.426 --> 00:07:26.856 A:middle
Intent values, those values will

00:07:26.856 --> 00:07:28.266 A:middle
be passed back to you with the

00:07:28.266 --> 00:07:28.836 A:middle
next message.

00:07:28.836 --> 00:07:30.766 A:middle
Let's see how you might use

00:07:30.766 --> 00:07:30.976 A:middle
them.

00:07:35.736 --> 00:07:36.846 A:middle
Let's say your customer is

00:07:36.846 --> 00:07:38.726 A:middle
browsing one of your products

00:07:39.016 --> 00:07:40.196 A:middle
and has a question about it.

00:07:41.576 --> 00:07:42.806 A:middle
You could use Chat Intent to

00:07:42.806 --> 00:07:44.626 A:middle
know the product config so your

00:07:44.626 --> 00:07:46.206 A:middle
customer doesn't need to type it

00:07:46.206 --> 00:07:46.506 A:middle
out.

00:07:48.356 --> 00:07:50.346 A:middle
For example, you could put the

00:07:50.346 --> 00:07:52.436 A:middle
product details or the product

00:07:52.436 --> 00:07:55.126 A:middle
code into the Intent field so

00:07:55.126 --> 00:07:56.556 A:middle
that your support agent can

00:07:56.556 --> 00:07:58.526 A:middle
provide a faster answer to your

00:07:58.786 --> 00:07:59.000 A:middle
customer.

00:08:01.216 --> 00:08:02.456 A:middle
Or maybe you have different

00:08:02.456 --> 00:08:04.066 A:middle
internal teams that offer

00:08:04.066 --> 00:08:06.476 A:middle
specialized support, you could

00:08:06.476 --> 00:08:07.666 A:middle
use Chat Intent to route

00:08:07.666 --> 00:08:08.946 A:middle
messages to the relevant

00:08:08.996 --> 00:08:09.786 A:middle
internal team.

00:08:11.746 --> 00:08:12.846 A:middle
In this case, you could put the

00:08:12.896 --> 00:08:14.686 A:middle
team code into the group field

00:08:15.136 --> 00:08:16.236 A:middle
and that way you could route

00:08:16.236 --> 00:08:17.846 A:middle
incoming messages to the team

00:08:17.846 --> 00:08:19.296 A:middle
that handles that particular

00:08:19.296 --> 00:08:19.626 A:middle
issue.

00:08:20.206 --> 00:08:24.466 A:middle
And sometimes your customers may

00:08:24.466 --> 00:08:25.956 A:middle
want to chat with one of your

00:08:25.956 --> 00:08:27.206 A:middle
particular locations.

00:08:28.376 --> 00:08:29.996 A:middle
In the future, you will be able

00:08:29.996 --> 00:08:32.346 A:middle
to provide your locations and

00:08:32.346 --> 00:08:34.886 A:middle
your location IDs to Apple Maps.

00:08:35.586 --> 00:08:37.126 A:middle
Apple will automatically then

00:08:37.186 --> 00:08:39.406 A:middle
populate the Intent field with

00:08:39.406 --> 00:08:40.556 A:middle
your location ID.

00:08:41.566 --> 00:08:43.506 A:middle
That way when the customer taps

00:08:43.576 --> 00:08:47.296 A:middle
the message and sends their

00:08:47.296 --> 00:08:49.066 A:middle
message to that location, you

00:08:49.066 --> 00:08:51.076 A:middle
will know to which location they

00:08:51.076 --> 00:08:53.216 A:middle
were directing their message and

00:08:53.216 --> 00:08:54.236 A:middle
then you will be able to route

00:08:54.236 --> 00:08:55.276 A:middle
the message appropriately.

00:08:55.926 --> 00:09:00.036 A:middle
So we just reviewed all the ways

00:09:00.036 --> 00:09:01.606 A:middle
that your business might be

00:09:01.606 --> 00:09:02.556 A:middle
found by your customer.

00:09:03.386 --> 00:09:05.246 A:middle
But once your customer taps that

00:09:05.246 --> 00:09:07.196 A:middle
Message button, they are then

00:09:07.196 --> 00:09:09.156 A:middle
taken to your conversation

00:09:09.626 --> 00:09:10.836 A:middle
inside of the Messages app.

00:09:11.816 --> 00:09:12.956 A:middle
So let's explore some of the

00:09:12.956 --> 00:09:14.726 A:middle
features of those Business Chat

00:09:14.726 --> 00:09:15.586 A:middle
conversations.

00:09:16.156 --> 00:09:19.956 A:middle
It's important to note that your

00:09:19.956 --> 00:09:21.426 A:middle
customer must send the first

00:09:21.426 --> 00:09:23.006 A:middle
message to open the

00:09:23.006 --> 00:09:23.726 A:middle
conversation.

00:09:24.336 --> 00:09:25.976 A:middle
But once that conversation is

00:09:25.976 --> 00:09:28.016 A:middle
open, you can then message back

00:09:28.516 --> 00:09:30.206 A:middle
or send important notifications.

00:09:31.666 --> 00:09:33.126 A:middle
With your customer's message,

00:09:33.806 --> 00:09:35.226 A:middle
you will also receive that

00:09:35.226 --> 00:09:37.046 A:middle
customer's opaque ID.

00:09:38.186 --> 00:09:40.376 A:middle
This is a unique ID designed to

00:09:40.426 --> 00:09:42.816 A:middle
preserve their anonymity until

00:09:42.816 --> 00:09:43.716 A:middle
they're ready to share more

00:09:43.746 --> 00:09:45.136 A:middle
personal information with you.

00:09:45.776 --> 00:09:48.476 A:middle
In addition, you will also

00:09:48.476 --> 00:09:50.896 A:middle
receive the customer's language

00:09:51.396 --> 00:09:53.956 A:middle
and device region so that you

00:09:53.956 --> 00:09:55.396 A:middle
can route their message to the

00:09:55.396 --> 00:09:57.276 A:middle
internal team that's best

00:09:57.276 --> 00:09:58.626 A:middle
equipped to answer their

00:09:58.626 --> 00:09:58.976 A:middle
question.

00:09:59.676 --> 00:10:04.016 A:middle
As we saw in the video, the

00:10:04.016 --> 00:10:05.796 A:middle
conversation session is long

00:10:05.796 --> 00:10:06.006 A:middle
lived.

00:10:06.916 --> 00:10:09.336 A:middle
Your customer can return and

00:10:09.336 --> 00:10:10.636 A:middle
pick up where they left off at

00:10:10.636 --> 00:10:11.206 A:middle
any time.

00:10:12.296 --> 00:10:13.666 A:middle
They should be able to just jump

00:10:13.666 --> 00:10:15.066 A:middle
in and ask a quick question

00:10:15.376 --> 00:10:16.906 A:middle
without having to re-identify

00:10:16.906 --> 00:10:17.546 A:middle
themselves.

00:10:18.396 --> 00:10:19.646 A:middle
And you can have their account

00:10:19.646 --> 00:10:21.696 A:middle
information ready so they can

00:10:21.696 --> 00:10:23.536 A:middle
get help without wasting time

00:10:23.536 --> 00:10:24.916 A:middle
describing what you should

00:10:24.916 --> 00:10:28.936 A:middle
already know.

00:10:29.376 --> 00:10:30.676 A:middle
After your customer sends the

00:10:30.676 --> 00:10:32.416 A:middle
first message, you might need

00:10:32.416 --> 00:10:34.346 A:middle
some personal details to assist

00:10:34.406 --> 00:10:34.556 A:middle
them.

00:10:34.926 --> 00:10:36.376 A:middle
So let's say you needed their

00:10:36.376 --> 00:10:36.986 A:middle
phone number.

00:10:37.236 --> 00:10:40.296 A:middle
You might ask and the QuickType

00:10:40.296 --> 00:10:42.026 A:middle
keyboard will make intelligent

00:10:42.026 --> 00:10:44.136 A:middle
suggestions so your customer can

00:10:44.136 --> 00:10:47.226 A:middle
reply with just a tap.

00:10:47.666 --> 00:10:48.966 A:middle
The QuickType keyboard can make

00:10:48.966 --> 00:10:50.666 A:middle
intelligent suggestions so your

00:10:50.666 --> 00:10:52.226 A:middle
customers can easily provide

00:10:52.226 --> 00:10:54.586 A:middle
their email address, their phone

00:10:54.586 --> 00:10:56.996 A:middle
number, their postal address,

00:10:57.566 --> 00:11:01.506 A:middle
and even their location.

00:11:02.116 --> 00:11:04.636 A:middle
Messages is a very personal

00:11:04.706 --> 00:11:05.026 A:middle
area.

00:11:05.616 --> 00:11:07.046 A:middle
This is where your customers

00:11:07.046 --> 00:11:08.456 A:middle
communicate with their friends

00:11:08.456 --> 00:11:08.926 A:middle
and family.

00:11:09.956 --> 00:11:11.826 A:middle
It's important to us that users

00:11:11.826 --> 00:11:13.506 A:middle
never receive unsolicited

00:11:13.506 --> 00:11:14.176 A:middle
messages.

00:11:14.916 --> 00:11:16.506 A:middle
We wanted to give users full

00:11:16.506 --> 00:11:17.396 A:middle
control over their

00:11:17.396 --> 00:11:18.936 A:middle
communications with businesses.

00:11:20.516 --> 00:11:21.436 A:middle
Users can manage their

00:11:21.436 --> 00:11:23.736 A:middle
conversations by hiding alerts

00:11:24.386 --> 00:11:25.836 A:middle
or by deleting the conversation.

00:11:26.426 --> 00:11:29.696 A:middle
When they hide alerts, they will

00:11:29.696 --> 00:11:31.706 A:middle
continue to receive messages but

00:11:31.706 --> 00:11:32.766 A:middle
they won't be notified.

00:11:33.496 --> 00:11:34.246 A:middle
And if they delete the

00:11:34.246 --> 00:11:36.066 A:middle
conversation, that will block

00:11:36.166 --> 00:11:37.546 A:middle
all future messages from you.

00:11:38.166 --> 00:11:40.456 A:middle
Next, attachments.

00:11:40.666 --> 00:11:44.546 A:middle
Because Business Chat is within

00:11:44.546 --> 00:11:46.216 A:middle
the Messages app, Business Chat

00:11:46.216 --> 00:11:47.656 A:middle
supports all of the standard

00:11:47.656 --> 00:11:49.796 A:middle
attachment types like photos,

00:11:50.446 --> 00:11:52.596 A:middle
videos, and documents.

00:11:53.746 --> 00:11:55.546 A:middle
For example, your customer might

00:11:55.616 --> 00:11:57.386 A:middle
send a photo of a product they

00:11:57.386 --> 00:11:59.796 A:middle
might need, or your customer

00:11:59.796 --> 00:12:01.806 A:middle
might send a video of an area of

00:12:01.806 --> 00:12:03.626 A:middle
their house to help you provide

00:12:03.626 --> 00:12:05.936 A:middle
a more accurate quote and you

00:12:05.936 --> 00:12:07.776 A:middle
can use attachments to send

00:12:07.776 --> 00:12:09.126 A:middle
forms or other important

00:12:09.126 --> 00:12:09.706 A:middle
information.

00:12:13.216 --> 00:12:15.056 A:middle
Next, let's cover some ways that

00:12:15.056 --> 00:12:16.456 A:middle
you can provide a better

00:12:16.456 --> 00:12:17.766 A:middle
experience to your customers.

00:12:18.956 --> 00:12:20.016 A:middle
We wanted to create some

00:12:20.016 --> 00:12:22.046 A:middle
built-in features that help you

00:12:22.046 --> 00:12:24.346 A:middle
provide a consistent engaging

00:12:24.346 --> 00:12:26.326 A:middle
experience for some common use

00:12:26.326 --> 00:12:26.766 A:middle
cases.

00:12:27.776 --> 00:12:29.306 A:middle
It's important to note that

00:12:29.306 --> 00:12:31.426 A:middle
these features are built in, so

00:12:31.426 --> 00:12:32.926 A:middle
they're available for you even

00:12:32.926 --> 00:12:34.286 A:middle
if you don't have your own app.

00:12:36.296 --> 00:12:38.266 A:middle
The first is Time Picker.

00:12:39.676 --> 00:12:41.226 A:middle
Scheduling appointments is a

00:12:41.266 --> 00:12:42.306 A:middle
common use case.

00:12:43.626 --> 00:12:45.356 A:middle
You can use Time Picker to send

00:12:45.356 --> 00:12:47.566 A:middle
over a list of proposed times to

00:12:47.566 --> 00:12:48.636 A:middle
your customer to review.

00:12:49.776 --> 00:12:51.366 A:middle
Your customer can see if they

00:12:51.366 --> 00:12:53.176 A:middle
have a conflict with existing

00:12:53.176 --> 00:12:54.176 A:middle
appointments that they might

00:12:54.176 --> 00:12:54.956 A:middle
have in Calendar.

00:12:56.316 --> 00:12:58.196 A:middle
Your customer can review and

00:12:58.196 --> 00:13:00.246 A:middle
then choose the best option and

00:13:00.326 --> 00:13:04.206 A:middle
send their choice back to you.

00:13:04.526 --> 00:13:06.116 A:middle
Choosing from a list of options

00:13:06.116 --> 00:13:07.706 A:middle
is also another common use case.

00:13:08.726 --> 00:13:09.956 A:middle
We created List Picker so you

00:13:09.956 --> 00:13:11.876 A:middle
can provide a visual way to make

00:13:11.876 --> 00:13:12.436 A:middle
a selection.

00:13:14.656 --> 00:13:16.246 A:middle
With List Picker, you can send

00:13:16.246 --> 00:13:18.096 A:middle
your customer a list of options.

00:13:18.966 --> 00:13:21.016 A:middle
Your customer can select one or

00:13:21.016 --> 00:13:22.686 A:middle
more, depending on how you

00:13:22.686 --> 00:13:25.106 A:middle
configured it, and then send a

00:13:25.106 --> 00:13:26.156 A:middle
choice back to you.

00:13:29.296 --> 00:13:30.716 A:middle
Lastly, we know that payments is

00:13:30.716 --> 00:13:31.856 A:middle
another common use case.

00:13:32.596 --> 00:13:34.796 A:middle
Apple Pay provides an easy and

00:13:34.796 --> 00:13:37.876 A:middle
secure way to pay.

00:13:38.076 --> 00:13:39.306 A:middle
And if you're also a retailer

00:13:39.306 --> 00:13:40.516 A:middle
that wants a quick check-out

00:13:40.546 --> 00:13:43.006 A:middle
process, customers can quickly

00:13:43.006 --> 00:13:44.526 A:middle
and securely provide their

00:13:44.676 --> 00:13:47.186 A:middle
payment, shipping, and contact

00:13:47.186 --> 00:13:49.196 A:middle
information and then check out

00:13:49.276 --> 00:13:49.966 A:middle
with just one touch.

00:13:55.356 --> 00:13:57.416 A:middle
The built-in features that we

00:13:57.416 --> 00:13:58.886 A:middle
just covered offer a great

00:13:58.886 --> 00:14:00.486 A:middle
experience for some common use

00:14:00.486 --> 00:14:00.866 A:middle
cases.

00:14:01.366 --> 00:14:02.726 A:middle
But we know that these just

00:14:02.726 --> 00:14:04.076 A:middle
scratch the surface of what's

00:14:04.076 --> 00:14:04.396 A:middle
needed.

00:14:05.346 --> 00:14:06.936 A:middle
To customize the experience for

00:14:06.936 --> 00:14:09.156 A:middle
your business, you can extend

00:14:09.156 --> 00:14:10.706 A:middle
Business Chat by using the

00:14:10.786 --> 00:14:12.566 A:middle
iMessage app framework released

00:14:12.566 --> 00:14:14.476 A:middle
last year in iOS 10.

00:14:15.096 --> 00:14:18.936 A:middle
With the Messages framework, you

00:14:18.936 --> 00:14:20.986 A:middle
can create app experiences that

00:14:20.986 --> 00:14:22.736 A:middle
your customers can use directly

00:14:22.736 --> 00:14:23.906 A:middle
within Business Chat.

00:14:24.636 --> 00:14:26.686 A:middle
Essentially, you can pull in

00:14:26.686 --> 00:14:28.156 A:middle
parts of your app into the

00:14:28.156 --> 00:14:30.116 A:middle
conversation just when your

00:14:30.166 --> 00:14:31.086 A:middle
customer needs it.

00:14:32.226 --> 00:14:33.456 A:middle
Your app can appear like a

00:14:33.456 --> 00:14:34.136 A:middle
message bubble.

00:14:34.656 --> 00:14:36.386 A:middle
For example, if the customer

00:14:36.386 --> 00:14:37.706 A:middle
needed to select their seats,

00:14:38.186 --> 00:14:39.126 A:middle
they could get a bubble like

00:14:39.216 --> 00:14:42.436 A:middle
this, tap it, and then quickly

00:14:42.436 --> 00:14:43.000 A:middle
complete the task.

00:14:47.516 --> 00:14:53.596 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:14:54.096 --> 00:14:55.896 A:middle
With iMessage apps, you can

00:14:56.046 --> 00:14:57.616 A:middle
speed customers through common

00:14:57.616 --> 00:14:59.436 A:middle
issues and improve your support

00:14:59.436 --> 00:15:00.326 A:middle
team productivity.

00:15:02.606 --> 00:15:04.456 A:middle
And Business Chat is a great way

00:15:04.456 --> 00:15:06.176 A:middle
to introduce customers to your

00:15:06.176 --> 00:15:06.356 A:middle
app.

00:15:07.496 --> 00:15:08.816 A:middle
If your customer doesn't yet

00:15:08.816 --> 00:15:10.426 A:middle
have your app installed, they

00:15:10.426 --> 00:15:12.016 A:middle
can tap to get the app right

00:15:12.116 --> 00:15:14.000 A:middle
from within the conversation.

00:15:17.326 --> 00:15:18.256 A:middle
You can use your app to

00:15:18.256 --> 00:15:20.436 A:middle
customize the look and behavior

00:15:20.436 --> 00:15:22.306 A:middle
of Messages using Live Message

00:15:22.306 --> 00:15:22.706 A:middle
layouts.

00:15:24.416 --> 00:15:25.706 A:middle
You can customize the bubble,

00:15:25.706 --> 00:15:27.766 A:middle
for example, by adding a map or

00:15:27.766 --> 00:15:30.456 A:middle
a live countdown, a simple form,

00:15:31.576 --> 00:15:33.176 A:middle
or any other interaction that

00:15:33.176 --> 00:15:35.306 A:middle
you create using your app.

00:15:35.856 --> 00:15:39.036 A:middle
To learn more about how to

00:15:39.036 --> 00:15:40.946 A:middle
create iMessage apps, go to

00:15:41.186 --> 00:15:44.526 A:middle
developer.apple.com/imessage.

00:15:45.326 --> 00:15:49.416 A:middle
Next, let's talk about getting

00:15:49.416 --> 00:15:49.926 A:middle
connected.

00:15:50.656 --> 00:15:53.886 A:middle
As a business, you're going to

00:15:53.886 --> 00:15:55.666 A:middle
need a customer service platform

00:15:55.946 --> 00:15:57.216 A:middle
that supports Business Chat.

00:15:58.756 --> 00:15:59.926 A:middle
Your platform will help you

00:15:59.926 --> 00:16:01.856 A:middle
connect, route messages

00:16:01.856 --> 00:16:03.636 A:middle
internally, and provide

00:16:03.786 --> 00:16:04.826 A:middle
productivity tools for your

00:16:04.826 --> 00:16:05.116 A:middle
team.

00:16:06.766 --> 00:16:08.326 A:middle
Your platform will also help

00:16:08.326 --> 00:16:10.116 A:middle
connect your apps into your

00:16:10.116 --> 00:16:11.226 A:middle
support operations.

00:16:12.526 --> 00:16:13.936 A:middle
This is so that your team can

00:16:13.936 --> 00:16:16.796 A:middle
send app experiences to your

00:16:18.576 --> 00:16:18.826 A:middle
customers.

00:16:19.146 --> 00:16:21.316 A:middle
As a business, you need to apply

00:16:21.416 --> 00:16:23.326 A:middle
for the developer preview at

00:16:23.326 --> 00:16:24.696 A:middle
register.apple.com.

00:16:26.296 --> 00:16:28.186 A:middle
Likewise, if you are a customer

00:16:28.186 --> 00:16:29.646 A:middle
service platform that supports

00:16:29.646 --> 00:16:31.976 A:middle
Messaging, you can also apply to

00:16:32.006 --> 00:16:33.296 A:middle
offer Business Chat to your

00:16:33.296 --> 00:16:34.776 A:middle
clients too.

00:16:37.856 --> 00:16:39.996 A:middle
So once your account is approved

00:16:39.996 --> 00:16:42.056 A:middle
for Business Chat, you could

00:16:42.056 --> 00:16:43.226 A:middle
receive messages from Apple

00:16:43.226 --> 00:16:43.816 A:middle
devices.

00:16:44.816 --> 00:16:45.946 A:middle
Let's say your customer sends a

00:16:45.946 --> 00:16:46.596 A:middle
message to you.

00:16:46.836 --> 00:16:48.546 A:middle
This message will first arrive

00:16:48.546 --> 00:16:50.146 A:middle
on Apple's Business Chat server.

00:16:51.076 --> 00:16:52.966 A:middle
From there, messages are passed

00:16:52.966 --> 00:16:54.156 A:middle
to your customer service

00:16:54.156 --> 00:16:58.056 A:middle
platform, and then your platform

00:16:58.366 --> 00:17:00.076 A:middle
will route messages to the

00:17:00.076 --> 00:17:01.626 A:middle
appropriate person or team

00:17:01.836 --> 00:17:02.866 A:middle
within your business.

00:17:03.536 --> 00:17:05.876 A:middle
When they respond, your message

00:17:05.876 --> 00:17:07.096 A:middle
is routed back to your customer.

00:17:07.676 --> 00:17:10.446 A:middle
As I mentioned, during Business

00:17:10.446 --> 00:17:12.596 A:middle
Chat developer preview, your

00:17:12.596 --> 00:17:13.996 A:middle
business is not yet publicly

00:17:13.996 --> 00:17:14.566 A:middle
accessible.

00:17:15.536 --> 00:17:17.186 A:middle
However, you can white list

00:17:17.186 --> 00:17:19.076 A:middle
employees and these employees

00:17:19.076 --> 00:17:20.606 A:middle
can test the full experience,

00:17:21.266 --> 00:17:22.476 A:middle
interact with your iMessage

00:17:22.476 --> 00:17:23.936 A:middle
apps, and make sure that

00:17:23.936 --> 00:17:25.536 A:middle
everything is working properly.

00:17:26.216 --> 00:17:30.516 A:middle
OK, let's go through how to get

00:17:30.516 --> 00:17:30.956 A:middle
started.

00:17:31.776 --> 00:17:33.726 A:middle
There are three things that you

00:17:33.726 --> 00:17:34.506 A:middle
can do today.

00:17:35.026 --> 00:17:36.956 A:middle
First, start developing.

00:17:37.476 --> 00:17:38.756 A:middle
You can use the Business Chat

00:17:38.756 --> 00:17:40.326 A:middle
Sandbox that Scotty will take us

00:17:40.326 --> 00:17:41.036 A:middle
through next.

00:17:42.026 --> 00:17:44.556 A:middle
Second, get connected on a

00:17:44.606 --> 00:17:46.066 A:middle
customer service platform that

00:17:46.066 --> 00:17:47.146 A:middle
supports Business Chat.

00:17:48.196 --> 00:17:50.616 A:middle
And then, apply for early access

00:17:50.616 --> 00:17:51.986 A:middle
to Business Chat.

00:17:53.536 --> 00:17:55.876 A:middle
With that, Scotty will take us

00:17:55.876 --> 00:17:57.006 A:middle
through a demo Business Chat

00:17:57.006 --> 00:17:59.026 A:middle
Sandbox and how you can use it

00:17:59.026 --> 00:18:01.376 A:middle
to start developing and testing

00:18:01.406 --> 00:18:02.476 A:middle
your use cases.

00:18:03.516 --> 00:18:07.500 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:18:12.816 --> 00:18:14.786 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Alright, thanks, Grant.

00:18:16.246 --> 00:18:17.516 A:middle
We're real excited about

00:18:17.516 --> 00:18:18.106 A:middle
Business Chat.

00:18:18.846 --> 00:18:20.336 A:middle
We have developed an entire

00:18:20.486 --> 00:18:21.906 A:middle
platform that will allow

00:18:21.906 --> 00:18:23.386 A:middle
everyone to communicate with

00:18:23.386 --> 00:18:25.496 A:middle
businesses directly through one

00:18:25.496 --> 00:18:26.986 A:middle
of the most used apps on the

00:18:27.086 --> 00:18:28.056 A:middle
planet, Messages.

00:18:29.466 --> 00:18:31.186 A:middle
And, as you've seen, we've built

00:18:31.186 --> 00:18:32.576 A:middle
in some great software into

00:18:32.576 --> 00:18:34.676 A:middle
every iOS 11 device that makes

00:18:34.676 --> 00:18:36.176 A:middle
performing these common business

00:18:36.176 --> 00:18:39.216 A:middle
tasks simple and fun, including

00:18:39.216 --> 00:18:41.416 A:middle
making payments using Apple Pay,

00:18:41.976 --> 00:18:43.676 A:middle
way better than trying to give

